.\" Man page for our implementatin of the UNIX sort program
.\" Cuervo & Oge - Spring 2015

.TH sort 1 "04 April 2015" "CSCI 241" "Oberlin College"

.SH NAME
.B sort
\- a program to sort lines of text!

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./sort
[ optional sorting flags ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
This program reads lines from standard input and sorts them, by default alphabetically.

.SH OPTIONS
.IP "-f"
This flag
.B f
olds lowercase letters into uppercase ones (i.e., case insensitive comparisons).
sort lines based on a leading number

.IP "-n"
Sorts lines based on the leading
.B n
umber.
.IP
.I Note:
The flag ignores leading whitespace.

.IP "-r"
.B R
everses the order of the sort.

.IP "-h or -?"
Brings up the
.B h
elp note and returns with a non-zero exit value.

.SH AUTHORS
Andres Cuervo and Alexandre Oge (Spring 2015)

.SH BUGS
    None!
